TITLE: Dumping Expressions at Runtime in V
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to use the dump() function for debugging and tracing expression values at runtime, illustrated with a factorial function example.
SOURCE: https://github.com/vlang/v/blob/master/doc/docs.md#2025-04-21_snippet_90

LANGUAGE: v
CODE:
```
fn factorial(n u32) u32 {
	if dump(n <= 1) {
		return dump(1)
	}
	return dump(n * factorial(n - 1))
}

fn main() {
	println(factorial(5))
}
```

