TITLE: Creating Recursive Structures with Sum Types in V
DESCRIPTION: Illustrates how to build recursive structures using sum types in V. The example implements a binary tree and a function to sum all node values.
SOURCE: https://github.com/vlang/v/blob/master/doc/docs.md#2025-04-21_snippet_114

LANGUAGE: v
CODE:
```
// V's binary tree
struct Empty {}

struct Node {
	value f64
	left  Tree
	right Tree
}

type Tree = Empty | Node

// sum up all node values

fn sum(tree Tree) f64 {
	return match tree {
		Empty { 0 }
		Node { tree.value + sum(tree.left) + sum(tree.right) }
	}
}

fn main() {
	left := Node{0.2, Empty{}, Empty{}}
	right := Node{0.3, Empty{}, Node{0.4, Empty{}, Empty{}}}
	tree := Node{0.5, left, right}
	println(sum(tree)) // 0.2 + 0.3 + 0.4 + 0.5 = 1.4
}
```

