TITLE: Parsing and Managing Txtar Archives in V
DESCRIPTION: This V code snippet demonstrates how to parse a txtar archive, unpack its contents to a directory, and then pack it back into a txtar archive. It relies on the 'encoding.txtar' module. The snippet illustrates creating a txtar archive with file entries, unpacking it to a temporary directory, and then packing it again to verify contents. Key dependencies include 'os' and 'encoding.txtar' modules. Expected inputs are strings representing txtar content, while outputs include assertions confirming file operations.
SOURCE: https://github.com/vlang/v/blob/master/vlib/encoding/txtar/README.md#2025-04-21_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: v
CODE:
```
import os
import encoding.txtar

a := txtar.parse('comment
line1
line2
-- file.txt --
some content that will go into file.txt
some more content
-- a/b/c/file.v --
import os
dump(os.args)
-- bcd/def/another.v --
dump(2+2)
')
assert a.files.len == 2
assert a.files[0].path == 'file.txt'
assert a.files[2].path == 'bcd/def/another.v'

tfolder := os.join_path(os.temp_dir(), 'xyz')
txtar.unpack(a, tfolder)!
assert os.exists(os.join_path(tfolder, 'bcd/def/another.v'))
b := txtar.pack(tfolder, '')!
assert b.files.len == a.files.len
os.rmdir_all(tfolder)!
