TITLE: Slice Independence Based on Parent Array Capacity in V
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how appending to a parent array may affect or not affect child slices based on capacity and reallocation.
SOURCE: https://github.com/vlang/v/blob/master/doc/docs.md#2025-04-21_snippet_35

LANGUAGE: v
CODE:
```
mut a := []int{len: 5, cap: 6, init: 2}
mut b := unsafe { a[1..4] } // the contents of `b` uses part of the same memory, that is used by `a` too

a << 3
// still no reallocation of `a`, since `a.len` still fits in `a.cap`
b[2] = 13 // `a[3]` is modified, through the slice `b`.

a << 4
// the content of `a` has been reallocated now, and is independent from `b` (`cap` was exceeded by `len`)
b[1] = 3 // no change in `a`

println(a) // `[2, 2, 2, 13, 2, 3, 4]`
println(b) // `[2, 3, 13]`
```

