TITLE: Handling Comments and Blank Lines in CSV Reading in V Language
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to handle comment lines and blank rows when reading a CSV file. Lines starting with a specified comment character are ignored during the read process.
SOURCE: https://github.com/vlang/v/blob/master/vlib/encoding/csv/README_csv_reader.md#2025-04-21_snippet_9

LANGUAGE: v
CODE:
```
import encoding.csv

const txt = '\n# this is a comment line\na,b,c\n\n\n
0,1,2\n
3,4,5\n# another comment\n'

fn main() {
	mut csvr := csv.csv_reader(
		scr_buf:     txt.str
		scr_buf_len: txt.len
		comment:     `#` // line starting with # will be ignored
	)!;
	// scan all rows, csvr.csv_map.len contain the valid
	// rows number in the CSV file.
	for row_index in 0 .. csvr.csv_map.len {
