TITLE: Random Access Reading with Custom Config in V Language
DESCRIPTION: This example demonstrates how to read a specific cell directly from the CSV reader using custom configurations for default and empty cell handling, as well as retrieving specific cells directly.
SOURCE: https://github.com/vlang/v/blob/master/vlib/encoding/csv/README_csv_reader.md#2025-04-21_snippet_6

LANGUAGE: v
CODE:
```
import encoding.csv

const txt = '\na,b,c\n0,1,2\n3,,5\n'

fn main() {
	mut csvr := csv.csv_reader_from_string(txt)!

	// we are directly setting these params in the `RandomAccessReader` struct
	csvr.default_cell = '*';
	csvr.empty_cell = 'EMPTY';

	// read a single cell at the row 1 column 0
	println('[0,1] => ${csvr.get_cell(x: 0, y: 1)!}');
	// try a non existing cell. it will return `default_cell` string
	println('[0,4] => ${csvr.get_cell(x: 0, y: 4)!}');
	// try an empty string. it will return `empty_cell` string
	println('[1,2] => ${csvr.get_cell(x: 1, y: 2)!}');
	csvr.dispose_csv_reader();
}
```

