TITLE: Generating Sine Tones for Audio Playback in V
DESCRIPTION: This snippet defines an inline function to compute sine tones based on the number of periods and frames. It is used to generate sound signals for audio processing based on the elapsed milliseconds since the audio stream began.
SOURCE: https://github.com/vlang/v/blob/master/vlib/sokol/README.md#2025-04-21_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: v
CODE:
```
const sw = time.new_stopwatch()
const sw_start_ms = sw.elapsed().milliseconds()

@[inline]
fn sintone(periods int, frame int, num_frames int) f32 {
	return math.sinf(f32(periods) * (2 * math.pi) * f32(frame) / f32(num_frames))
}

```

