TITLE: Noinit structs in V
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to create structs that cannot be initialized outside their module using the `[noinit]` attribute. These structs are meant to be used through factory functions that can implement validation logic.
SOURCE: https://github.com/vlang/v/blob/master/doc/docs.md#2025-04-21_snippet_73

LANGUAGE: v
CODE:
```
module sample

@[noinit]
pub struct Information {
pub:
	data string
}

pub fn new_information(data string) !Information {
	if data.len == 0 || data.len > 100 {
		return error('data must be between 1 and 100 characters')
	}
	return Information{
		data: data
	}
}
```

